# Coding Standards
   
## TypeScript Guidelines

- Follow TypeScript strict mode as configured in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)
- Use proper type annotations and avoid `any` types
- Implement interfaces for settings and configuration objects
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations

## Code Quality

- All code must pass ESLint checks (see [.eslintrc](mdc:.eslintrc))
- Run `npm run build` to ensure TypeScript compilation succeeds
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add comments for complex regex patterns and business logic

## Markdown Documentation

- All .md files must pass markdownlint checks
- Run `npm run lint:md` to validate markdown files
- Run `npm run lint:md:fix` to automatically fix formatting issues
- Maximum line length: 120 characters (excluding code blocks and tables)
- Use consistent heading styles and proper list formatting
- Specify language for code blocks

## Project Documentation

Project documentation is stored in README.md and the docs folder

When making changes:
1. Update @README.md for user-facing changes
2. Update @docs/*.md for technical changes
3. Ensure all markdown passes linting
4. Update examples if functionality changes
